cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.GT

This paper deals with the performance analysis of caching methods in a hierarchical network consisting of mobile users and cellular networks. The topic of caching and network performance is closely related to the field of network information theory (cs.IT) and network optimization (cs.NI). The use of Poisson point processes (PPP) is also a common tool in the analysis of wireless networks, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The study of content popularity models and their impact on network performance is also relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the analysis of network delay and performance can also be considered a topic in game theory (cs.GT).
